Power utility Eskom’s head of generation Matshela Koko, who was suspended earlier this month over allegations of graft, has submitted his resignation, according to reports on Friday.
A copy of Koko’s resignation letter, posted on Twitter by Moneyweb, said he was however not admitting to guilt over charges relating to the awarding of contracts to a company in which his stepdaughter owns shares.
Eskom officials were not immediately reachable to confirm the reports.






– African News Agency (ANA)
 
I don’t issue statements without approval of Eskom managers, says spokesperson

